{"word":"ἅλμη","slug":"ἅλμη","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἅλμη</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><el>ἅλς</el>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>sea-water, brine</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>: <i>spray that has dried on the skin</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>: <i>a salt incrustation</i> on soil, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>the brine, <a href='S:id est'>i. e.</a> <i>the sea</i>, <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}